Hm2AgentPortMask.name: Hm2AgentPortMask
Hm2AgentPortMask.description: Each octet within this value specifies a set of eight ports, with the first octet specifying ports 1 through 8, the second octet specifying ports 9 through 16, etc. Within each octet, the most significant bit represents the lowest numbered port, and the least significant bit represents the highest numbered port. Thus, each port of the bridge is represented by a single bit within the value of this object. If that bit has a value of '1' then that port is included in the set of ports, the port is not included if its bit has a value of '0'. When setting this value, the system will ignore configuration for ports not between the first and last valid ports. Configuration of any port numbers between this range that are not valid ports return a failure message, but will still apply configuration for valid ports.

LagList.name: LagList
LagList.description: Each octet within this value specifies a set of eight LAGs, with the first octet specifying LAG 1 through 8, the second octet specifying LAG 9 through 16, etc. Within each octet, the most significant bit represents LAG1, and the least significant bit represents LAGn. Thus, each LAG of the bridge is represented by a single bit within the value of this object. If that bit has a value of '1' then that LAG is configured; the LAG is not configured if its bit has a value of '0'.

VlanList.name: VlanList
VlanList.description: Each octet within this value specifies a set of eight vlans, with the first octet specifying vlans 1 through 8, the second octet specifying vlans 9 through 16, etc. Within each octet, the most significant bit represents the lowest numbered vlan, and the least significant bit represents the highest numbered vlan. Thus, each vlan supported is represented by a single bit within the value of this object. If that bit has a value of '1' then the associated port is in that VLAN, the port is not included if the vlans bit has a value of '0'.

Ipv6IfIndex.name: Ipv6IfIndex
Ipv6IfIndex.description: A unique value, greater than zero for each internetwork layer interface in the managed system. It is recommended that values are assigned contiguously starting from 1. The value for each internetwork layer interface must remain constant at least from one reinitialization of the entity's network management system to the next reinitialization.

Ipv6IfIndexOrZero.name: Ipv6IfIndexOrZero
Ipv6IfIndexOrZero.description: This textual convention is an extension of the Ipv6IfIndex convention. The latter defines a greater than zero value used to identify an IPv6 interface in the managed system. This extension permits the additional value of zero. The value zero is object specific and must therefore be defined as part of the description of any object which uses this syntax. Examples of the usage of zero might include situations where the interface was unknown, or when none or all interfaces need to be referenced.

hm2AgentLagConfigCreate.name: hm2AgentLagConfigCreate
hm2AgentLagConfigCreate.description: Agent LAG Create. When this object is set with a non-empty string with the format lag/<port>, a new LAG will be created if possible, with the entered string as its index. Get operation on this MIB object returns a null-value, as for the purpose of viewing the LAG index and details, the user should perform the traversal of hm2AgentLagSummaryConfigTable. For this reason the get operation on this object hm2AgentLagConfigCreate becomes insignificant.

hm2AgentSwitchSnoopingPortMask.name: hm2AgentSwitchSnoopingPortMask
hm2AgentSwitchSnoopingPortMask.description: IGMP/MLD Snooping Port Mask. This allows configuration of IGMP/MLD Snooping on selected ports. IGMP/MLD Snooping cannot be enabled on an interface that has routing enabled, or is a member of a LAG. If a port which has IGMP/MLD Snooping enabled becomes enabled for routing, or is enlisted as a member of a LAG, IGMP/MLD Snooping functionality will be disabled on that port. IGMP/MLD Snooping functionality will be subsequently be reenabled if routing is disabled or LAG membership is removed from an interface that had previously had IGMP/MLD Snooping enabled. To obtain port numbers from interface numbers, use the objects hm2AgentPortDot1dBasePort and hm2AgentPortIfIndex in the hm2AgentPortConfigTable table.

hm2AgentSwitchSnoopingQuerierAdminMode.name: hm2AgentSwitchSnoopingQuerierAdminMode
hm2AgentSwitchSnoopingQuerierAdminMode.description: This enables or disables Snooping Querier on the system.

hm2AgentSwitchSnoopingQuerierVersion.name: hm2AgentSwitchSnoopingQuerierVersion
hm2AgentSwitchSnoopingQuerierVersion.description: This specifies the multicast protocol versions that are supported by the system.

hm2AgentSwitchSnoopingQuerierQueryInterv.name: hm2AgentSwitchSnoopingQuerierQueryInterval
hm2AgentSwitchSnoopingQuerierQueryInterv.description: This specified the timer interval after which the system generates general queries.

hm2AgentSwitchSnoopingQuerierExpiryInter.name: hm2AgentSwitchSnoopingQuerierExpiryInterval
hm2AgentSwitchSnoopingQuerierExpiryInter.description: This specified the timer interval after which the detected other querier information is no longer valid.

hm2AgentSwitchSnoopingQuerierVlanTable.name: hm2AgentSwitchSnoopingQuerierVlanTable
hm2AgentSwitchSnoopingQuerierVlanTable.description: A table of the Snooping Querier Vlan configuration entries.

hm2AgentSwitchSnoopingQuerierVlanEntry.name: hm2AgentSwitchSnoopingQuerierVlanEntry
hm2AgentSwitchSnoopingQuerierVlanEntry.description: Represents entry for a Snooping Querier configurable Vlan.

hm2AgentSwitchSnoopingQuerierVlanAdminMo.name: hm2AgentSwitchSnoopingQuerierVlanAdminMode
hm2AgentSwitchSnoopingQuerierVlanAdminMo.description: This enables or disables Snooping Querier on a selected Vlan interface.

hm2AgentSwitchSnoopingQuerierVlanOperMod.name: hm2AgentSwitchSnoopingQuerierVlanOperMode
hm2AgentSwitchSnoopingQuerierVlanOperMod.description: This specifies the current state of the Snooping Querier on a selected vlan interface

hm2AgentSwitchSnoopingQuerierElectionPar.name: hm2AgentSwitchSnoopingQuerierElectionParticipateMode
hm2AgentSwitchSnoopingQuerierElectionPar.description: This object is deprecated. This enables or disables the Snooping Querier Election Participation mode. When enabled snooping querier switch will participate in querier election up on discovering another querier in the specified vlan. When disabled, up on discovering another querier, snooping querier moves to non-querier state. The state of the querier is solely set by hm2AgentSwitchSnoopingQuerierVlanAdminMode. If hm2AgentSwitchSnoopingQuerierVlanAdminMode is set to enable(1) hm2AgentSwitchSnoopingQuerierElectionParticipateMode will be set internally to enable(1). If hm2AgentSwitchSnoopingQuerierVlanAdminMode is set to disable(2) hm2AgentSwitchSnoopingQuerierElectionParticipateMode will be set internally to disable(2).

hm2AgentSwitchSnoopingQuerierVlanAddress.name: hm2AgentSwitchSnoopingQuerierVlanAddress
hm2AgentSwitchSnoopingQuerierVlanAddress.description: This specifies the default source ip address to be used while generating general queries on the specified vlan.

hm2AgentSwitchSnoopingQuerierOperVersion.name: hm2AgentSwitchSnoopingQuerierOperVersion
hm2AgentSwitchSnoopingQuerierOperVersion.description: This specifies the multicast protocol version that is currently being used by the snooping switch for the specified vlan while generating query messages.

hm2AgentSwitchSnoopingQuerierOperMaxResp.name: hm2AgentSwitchSnoopingQuerierOperMaxResponseTime
hm2AgentSwitchSnoopingQuerierOperMaxResp.description: The amount of time in seconds a switch will wait after sending a query on the selected vlan because it did not receive a report for a particular group in the interface participating in the vlan. This object is valid only when hm2AgentSwitchSnoopingQuerierOperVersion object is valid. (-1) - indicates that parameter is not available; ( 0) - indicates that response time is less then 1 second.

hm2AgentSwitchSnoopingQuerierLastQuerier.name: hm2AgentSwitchSnoopingQuerierLastQuerierAddress
hm2AgentSwitchSnoopingQuerierLastQuerier.description: This specifies the last querier's ip address for the specified vlan. It represents the detected other multicast querier in the vlan.

hm2AgentSwitchSnoopingQuerierLastQuerier.name: hm2AgentSwitchSnoopingQuerierLastQuerierVersion
hm2AgentSwitchSnoopingQuerierLastQuerier.description: This specifies the multicast protocol version that is currently being used by the detected other multicast querier for the specified vlan. (-1) - indicates that parameter is not available.

hm2AgentPortMirrorTable.name: hm2AgentPortMirrorTable
hm2AgentPortMirrorTable.description: This table includes entries for each Port Mirroring session.

hm2AgentPortMirrorEntry.name: hm2AgentPortMirrorEntry
hm2AgentPortMirrorEntry.description: Provides configuration of a Port Mirroring session specifying the destination port, and the source Port Mask, providing a many-to-one mapping.

hm2AgentPortMirrorSessionNum.name: hm2AgentPortMirrorSessionNum
hm2AgentPortMirrorSessionNum.description: The Session number of this mirroring entry. The number of sessions is fixed and platform dependant.

hm2AgentPortMirrorDestinationPort.name: hm2AgentPortMirrorDestinationPort
hm2AgentPortMirrorDestinationPort.description: The port which traffic from the mirrored ports will be sent to.

hm2AgentPortMirrorSourcePortMask.name: hm2AgentPortMirrorSourcePortMask
hm2AgentPortMirrorSourcePortMask.description: The ports from which traffic will be sent to the destination port. The destination port can not be included in this list of ports.

hm2AgentPortMirrorAdminMode.name: hm2AgentPortMirrorAdminMode
hm2AgentPortMirrorAdminMode.description: The status of this port mirroring session. enable(1) - This session is active and all traffic from the source ports will be mirrored to the destination port. disable(2) - This session is not active.

hm2AgentPortMirrorSourceVlan.name: hm2AgentPortMirrorSourceVlan
hm2AgentPortMirrorSourceVlan.description: The vlan from which traffic will be sent to the destination port.

hm2AgentPortMirrorRemoteSourceVlan.name: hm2AgentPortMirrorRemoteSourceVlan
hm2AgentPortMirrorRemoteSourceVlan.description: The remote vlan from which traffic will be sent to the destination port.

hm2AgentPortMirrorRemoteDestinationVlan.name: hm2AgentPortMirrorRemoteDestinationVlan
hm2AgentPortMirrorRemoteDestinationVlan.description: The VLAN that forwards the network traffic to the destination switch.

hm2AgentPortMirrorReflectorPort.name: hm2AgentPortMirrorReflectorPort
hm2AgentPortMirrorReflectorPort.description: The port which traffic from the mirrored ports will be sent to in case of destination being remote VLAN.

hm2AgentPortMirrorAllowMgmtMode.name: hm2AgentPortMirrorAllowMgmtMode
hm2AgentPortMirrorAllowMgmtMode.description: The status of the management access possibility for this session. enable(1) - Management is allowed - The device is accessible via this port and is responsive to protocols while mirroring the probe port. disable(2) - Management not is allowed - the device is not accessible via this port and is not responsive to protocols. It only mirrors the probe port.

hm2AgentPortMirrorReset.name: hm2AgentPortMirrorReset
hm2AgentPortMirrorReset.description: Removes, reset(2) the configuration for this session. Returns always other(1) when read.

hm2AgentPortMirrorTypeTable.name: hm2AgentPortMirrorTypeTable
hm2AgentPortMirrorTypeTable.description: This table includes entries for each source ports direction of port mirroring.

hm2AgentPortMirrorTypeEntry.name: hm2AgentPortMirrorTypeEntry
hm2AgentPortMirrorTypeEntry.description: Provides configuration of a Port Mirroring direction specifying the session of the port mirroring and source port.

hm2AgentPortMirrorTypeSourcePort.name: hm2AgentPortMirrorTypeSourcePort
hm2AgentPortMirrorTypeSourcePort.description: The port from which traffic will be sent to the destination port. This port should be a source port in the corresponding session.

hm2AgentPortMirrorTypeType.name: hm2AgentPortMirrorTypeType
hm2AgentPortMirrorTypeType.description: The direction of the data to be mirrored on this source port. none(0) - No configuration is set. tx(1) - The data that is transmitted from the source port. rx(2) - The data that is received on the source port. txrx(3) - The data that is transmitted/received from/on the source port

hm2AgentPortMirrorRemoteVlan.name: hm2AgentPortMirrorRemoteVlan
hm2AgentPortMirrorRemoteVlan.description: The VLAN configured as RSPAN VLAN.

hm2AgentPortMirrorVlanMirrorPortConflict.name: hm2AgentPortMirrorVlanMirrorPortConflict
hm2AgentPortMirrorVlanMirrorPortConflict.description: VLAN has been already configured as a source interface. At the same time physical interface and VLAN interface cannot be configured as source interfaces for a session.

hm2AgentPortMirrorPortVlanMirrorConflict.name: hm2AgentPortMirrorPortVlanMirrorConflict
hm2AgentPortMirrorPortVlanMirrorConflict.description: A physical interface has been already configured as a source interface. At the same time physical interface and VLAN interface cannot be configured as source interfaces for a session.

hm2AgentPortMirrorProbePortVlanConflict.name: hm2AgentPortMirrorProbePortVlanConflict
hm2AgentPortMirrorProbePortVlanConflict.description: Destination interface cannot participate in source VLAN.

hm2AgentPortMirrorVlanNotCreated.name: hm2AgentPortMirrorVlanNotCreated
hm2AgentPortMirrorVlanNotCreated.description: Not existing VLAN cannot be configured as source interface for a session.

hm2AgentPortMirrorInvalidSourcePort.name: hm2AgentPortMirrorInvalidSourcePort
hm2AgentPortMirrorInvalidSourcePort.description: Selected interface () cannot be configured as source interface.

hm2AgentPortMirrorSourcePortDestinationP.name: hm2AgentPortMirrorSourcePortDestinationPortConflict
hm2AgentPortMirrorSourcePortDestinationP.description: Destination interface () cannot be configured as source interface.

hm2AgentPortMirrorDestinationPortInvalid.name: hm2AgentPortMirrorDestinationPortInvalid
hm2AgentPortMirrorDestinationPortInvalid.description: Conflict with another feature: Selected interface () is already used by () and cannot be configured as a destination interface.

hm2AgentPortMirrorVlanRspanVlanConflict.name: hm2AgentPortMirrorVlanRspanVlanConflict
hm2AgentPortMirrorVlanRspanVlanConflict.description: RSPAN vlan () cannot be configured as source vlan.

hm2AgentPortMirrorRemoteSourceRemoteDest.name: hm2AgentPortMirrorRemoteSourceRemoteDestinationConflict
hm2AgentPortMirrorRemoteSourceRemoteDest.description: Source and destination cannot be set to remote VLAN at the same time.

hm2AgentPortMirrorReflectorPortInvalid.name: hm2AgentPortMirrorReflectorPortInvalid
hm2AgentPortMirrorReflectorPortInvalid.description: Selected interface () cannot be configured as a reflector interface. Only physical interface can be configured as a reflector interface.

hm2AgentPortMirrorSourcePortReflectorPor.name: hm2AgentPortMirrorSourcePortReflectorPortConflict
hm2AgentPortMirrorSourcePortReflectorPor.description: Source interface () cannot be configured as reflector interface.

hm2AgentPortMirrorReflectorPortVlanConfl.name: hm2AgentPortMirrorReflectorPortVlanConflict
hm2AgentPortMirrorReflectorPortVlanConfl.description: Reflector interface () cannot participate in source vlan ().

hm2AgentPortMirrorPrivateVlanConfigured.name: hm2AgentPortMirrorPrivateVlanConfigured
hm2AgentPortMirrorPrivateVlanConfigured.description: Selected VLAN is already configured as private VLAN and cannot be configured as RSPAN VLAN.

hm2AgentPortMirrorDestinationRemotePortN.name: hm2AgentPortMirrorDestinationRemotePortNotSet
hm2AgentPortMirrorDestinationRemotePortN.description: A destination/reflector port must first be set before mirroring/remote-mirroring can be enabled.

hm2AgentPortMirrorRspanVlanInconsistent.name: hm2AgentPortMirrorRspanVlanInconsistent
hm2AgentPortMirrorRspanVlanInconsistent.description: The RSPAN VLAN ID is inconsistent with the RSPAN source/destination VLAN ID.

hm2AgentPortMirrorRspanVlanIdInvalid.name: hm2AgentPortMirrorRspanVlanIdInvalid
hm2AgentPortMirrorRspanVlanIdInvalid.description: VLAN 1 cannot be used as the RSPAN VLAN.

hm2AgentDot3adAggPortTable.name: hm2AgentDot3adAggPortTable
hm2AgentDot3adAggPortTable.description: This table provides 802.3ad link aggregation information for each physical port that is not available through the standard MIB.

hm2AgentDot3adAggPortEntry.name: hm2AgentDot3adAggPortEntry
hm2AgentDot3adAggPortEntry.description: Information about a table entry. The hm2AgentDot3adAggPort identifies the external interface number of the port.

hm2AgentPortConfigTable.name: hm2AgentPortConfigTable
hm2AgentPortConfigTable.description: A table of the switch's physical port config entries

hm2AgentPortClearStats.name: hm2AgentPortClearStats
hm2AgentPortClearStats.description: Clear stats for this port only.

hm2AgentPortDot3FlowControlMode.name: hm2AgentPortDot3FlowControlMode
hm2AgentPortDot3FlowControlMode.description: Config flowcontrol allows you to enable or disable 802.3x flow control for this port. This value applies to only full-duplex mode ports. Enabling symmetric flow control allows the port to send and receive pause frames. Enabling asymmetric flow control allows the port to receive pause frames but it will not transmit pause frames.

hm2AgentPortMaxFrameSizeLimit.name: hm2AgentPortMaxFrameSizeLimit
hm2AgentPortMaxFrameSizeLimit.description: This object identifies the largest value that can be configured for hm2AgentPortMaxFrameSize.

hm2AgentPortMaxFrameSize.name: hm2AgentPortMaxFrameSize
hm2AgentPortMaxFrameSize.description: This object identifies the currently configured maximum frame size value for this port. The maximum value that this object can be set to is the value of hm2AgentPortMaxFrameSizeLimit. For Ethernet ports which support 802.1Q vlan tagging, the minimum value that this object can be set to is 1522

hm2AgentPortBroadcastControlMode.name: hm2AgentPortBroadcastControlMode
hm2AgentPortBroadcastControlMode.description: If enabled, broadcast storm recovery will function on this port. When you specify Enable for Broadcast Storm Recovery and the broadcast traffic on this Ethernet port exceeds the configured threshold, the switch blocks (discards) the broadcast traffic.

hm2AgentPortBroadcastControlThreshold.name: hm2AgentPortBroadcastControlThreshold
hm2AgentPortBroadcastControlThreshold.description: Configures the broadcast storm recovery threshold for this port as a percentage of port speed or as an absolute pps rate.

hm2AgentPortMulticastControlMode.name: hm2AgentPortMulticastControlMode
hm2AgentPortMulticastControlMode.description: If enabled, multicast storm recovery will function on this port. When you specify Enable for Multicast Storm Recovery and the multicast traffic on this Ethernet port exceeds the configured threshold, the switch blocks (discards) the multicast traffic.

hm2AgentPortMulticastControlThreshold.name: hm2AgentPortMulticastControlThreshold
hm2AgentPortMulticastControlThreshold.description: Configures the multicast storm recovery threshold for this port as a percentage of port speed or as an absolute pps rate.

hm2AgentPortUnicastControlMode.name: hm2AgentPortUnicastControlMode
hm2AgentPortUnicastControlMode.description: If enabled, unicast storm recovery will function on this port. When you specify Enable for Unicast Storm Recovery and the unknown unicast traffic on this Ethernet port exceeds the configured threshold, the switch blocks (discards) the unknown unicast traffic.

hm2AgentPortUnicastControlThreshold.name: hm2AgentPortUnicastControlThreshold
hm2AgentPortUnicastControlThreshold.description: Configures the unicast storm recovery threshold for this port as a percentage of port speed or as an absolute pps rate.

hm2AgentPortBroadcastControlThresholdUni.name: hm2AgentPortBroadcastControlThresholdUnit
hm2AgentPortBroadcastControlThresholdUni.description: Configures the units of the threshold value to percentage of port speed or absolute packets per second.

hm2AgentPortMulticastControlThresholdUni.name: hm2AgentPortMulticastControlThresholdUnit
hm2AgentPortMulticastControlThresholdUni.description: Configures the units of the threshold value to percentage of port speed or absolute packets per second.

hm2AgentPortUnicastControlThresholdUnit.name: hm2AgentPortUnicastControlThresholdUnit
hm2AgentPortUnicastControlThresholdUnit.description: Configures the units of the threshold value to percentage of port speed or absolute packets per second.

hm2AgentPortVoiceVlanMode.name: hm2AgentPortVoiceVlanMode
hm2AgentPortVoiceVlanMode.description: Describes and Configures the Port Voice VLAN Mode. This object can only be set to disable(5).

hm2AgentPortVoiceVlanID.name: hm2AgentPortVoiceVlanID
hm2AgentPortVoiceVlanID.description: Describes and Configures the Port Voice VLAN ID if the Voice Vlan Mode is Vlan ID.

hm2AgentPortVoiceVlanPriority.name: hm2AgentPortVoiceVlanPriority
hm2AgentPortVoiceVlanPriority.description: Describes and Configures the Port Voice VLAN Priority if the Voice Vlan Mode is dot1p. A value of 255 indicates that the priority is not configured.

hm2AgentPortVoiceVlanDataPriorityMode.name: hm2AgentPortVoiceVlanDataPriorityMode
hm2AgentPortVoiceVlanDataPriorityMode.description: Describes and Configures the Port Voice VLAN Data Priority Mode.

hm2AgentPortVoiceVlanOperationalStatus.name: hm2AgentPortVoiceVlanOperationalStatus
hm2AgentPortVoiceVlanOperationalStatus.description: Describes the Port Voice VLAN Operational Status.

hm2AgentPortVoiceVlanUntagged.name: hm2AgentPortVoiceVlanUntagged
hm2AgentPortVoiceVlanUntagged.description: Describes and Configures the Port Voice VLAN tagging mode.

hm2AgentPortVoiceVlanNoneMode.name: hm2AgentPortVoiceVlanNoneMode
hm2AgentPortVoiceVlanNoneMode.description: Describes and Configures the Port Voice VLAN None mode.

hm2AgentPortVoiceVlanDSCP.name: hm2AgentPortVoiceVlanDSCP
hm2AgentPortVoiceVlanDSCP.description: Describes and Configures the Port Voice VLAN DSCP value.

hm2AgentPortVoiceVlanAuthMode.name: hm2AgentPortVoiceVlanAuthMode
hm2AgentPortVoiceVlanAuthMode.description: Describes and Configures the Port Voice VLAN Authentication mode. Disable means authentication not required for voice devices when dot1x is enabled.

hm2AgentPortDot3FlowControlOperStatus.name: hm2AgentPortDot3FlowControlOperStatus
hm2AgentPortDot3FlowControlOperStatus.description: This object identifies operational status of the flow control per port.

hm2AgentPortSfpLinkLossAlert.name: hm2AgentPortSfpLinkLossAlert
hm2AgentPortSfpLinkLossAlert.description: If enabled, this object helps in the detecting the loss of a SFP link by deactivating its light.

hm2AgentProtocolGroupTable.name: hm2AgentProtocolGroupTable
hm2AgentProtocolGroupTable.description: A table of the switch's Protocol-based VLAN entries

hm2AgentProtocolGroupId.name: hm2AgentProtocolGroupId
hm2AgentProtocolGroupId.description: Group identifier of the Protocol-based VLAN entry.

hm2AgentProtocolGroupName.name: hm2AgentProtocolGroupName
hm2AgentProtocolGroupName.description: Group name of the Protocol-based VLAN entry.

hm2AgentProtocolGroupVlanId.name: hm2AgentProtocolGroupVlanId
hm2AgentProtocolGroupVlanId.description: VLAN associated with the Protocol-based VLAN entry. Set to 0 to remove.

hm2AgentProtocolGroupStatus.name: hm2AgentProtocolGroupStatus
hm2AgentProtocolGroupStatus.description: The status of the Protocol-based VLAN entry. active(1) - this entry is active createAndGo(4) - used to create a new entry destroy(6) - remove this entry

hm2AgentProtocolGroupPortTable.name: hm2AgentProtocolGroupPortTable
hm2AgentProtocolGroupPortTable.description: A table of the switch's physical port config entries

hm2AgentProtocolGroupPortIfIndex.name: hm2AgentProtocolGroupPortIfIndex
hm2AgentProtocolGroupPortIfIndex.description: The interface number of this instance.

hm2AgentProtocolGroupPortStatus.name: hm2AgentProtocolGroupPortStatus
hm2AgentProtocolGroupPortStatus.description: The status of this entry. active(1) - the port is associated with this group createAndGo(4) - add the port to this group createAndWait(5) - add the port to this group destroy(6) - remove the port from this group

hm2AgentProtocolGroupProtocolTable.name: hm2AgentProtocolGroupProtocolTable
hm2AgentProtocolGroupProtocolTable.description: A table of the switch's physical port config entries

hm2AgentProtocolGroupProtocolID.name: hm2AgentProtocolGroupProtocolID
hm2AgentProtocolGroupProtocolID.description: The protocol ID of this instance. The value for IP is 2048 (0x0800), ARP is 2054 (0x0806) and IPX is 33079 (0x8137). Other protocol Ids in the range 1536 to 65535 can also be configured.

hm2AgentProtocolGroupProtocolStatus.name: hm2AgentProtocolGroupProtocolStatus
hm2AgentProtocolGroupProtocolStatus.description: The status of this entry. active(1) - the port is associated with this group createAndGo(4) - add the port to this group createAndWait(5) - add the port to this group destroy(6) - remove the port from this group

hm2AgentStpConfigFormatSelector.name: hm2AgentStpConfigFormatSelector
hm2AgentStpConfigFormatSelector.description: The MST configuration format selector. A value other than 0 (zero) indicates non-support for the IEEE 802.1s standard.

hm2AgentStpConfigName.name: hm2AgentStpConfigName
hm2AgentStpConfigName.description: The MST configuration name of at most 32 characters.

hm2AgentStpConfigRevision.name: hm2AgentStpConfigRevision
hm2AgentStpConfigRevision.description: The MST configuration revision. The default value is 1.

hm2AgentStpForceVersion.name: hm2AgentStpForceVersion
hm2AgentStpForceVersion.description: The MST configuration force protocol version. The default version is RSTP.

hm2AgentStpAdminMode.name: hm2AgentStpAdminMode
hm2AgentStpAdminMode.description: The spanning tree operational status. enable(1) - enables spanning tree operational status on the switch. disable(2) - disables spanning tree operational status on the switch. The default status is enabled.

hm2AgentStpPortState.name: hm2AgentStpPortState
hm2AgentStpPortState.description: The administrative STP state for the port. enable(1) - enables STP on the port. disable(2) - disables STP on the port. The default port STP state is enabled for the first 4095 ports and disabled for any ports beyond.

hm2AgentStpPortStatsMstpBpduRx.name: hm2AgentStpPortStatsMstpBpduRx
hm2AgentStpPortStatsMstpBpduRx.description: The MSTP BPDUs received on a specific port.

hm2AgentStpPortStatsMstpBpduTx.name: hm2AgentStpPortStatsMstpBpduTx
hm2AgentStpPortStatsMstpBpduTx.description: The MSTP BPDUs sent from a specific port.

hm2AgentStpPortStatsRstpBpduRx.name: hm2AgentStpPortStatsRstpBpduRx
hm2AgentStpPortStatsRstpBpduRx.description: The RSTP BPDUs received on a specific port.

hm2AgentStpPortStatsRstpBpduTx.name: hm2AgentStpPortStatsRstpBpduTx
hm2AgentStpPortStatsRstpBpduTx.description: The RSTP BPDUs sent from a specific port.

hm2AgentStpPortStatsStpBpduRx.name: hm2AgentStpPortStatsStpBpduRx
hm2AgentStpPortStatsStpBpduRx.description: The STP BPDUs received on a specific port.

hm2AgentStpPortStatsStpBpduTx.name: hm2AgentStpPortStatsStpBpduTx
hm2AgentStpPortStatsStpBpduTx.description: The STP BPDUs sent from a specific port.

hm2AgentStpPortUpTime.name: hm2AgentStpPortUpTime
hm2AgentStpPortUpTime.description: Time since port was reset. It is displayed in days, hours, minutes, and seconds.

hm2AgentStpPortMigrationCheck.name: hm2AgentStpPortMigrationCheck
hm2AgentStpPortMigrationCheck.description: Force the specified port to transmit RSTP or MSTP BPDUs. Supported values: false(0) - BPDUs are not to be transmitted. true(1) - BPDUs are to be transmitted A non-zero value indicates that BPDUs are to be sent on the specified port.

hm2AgentStpCstHelloTime.name: hm2AgentStpCstHelloTime
hm2AgentStpCstHelloTime.description: The MSTP root port hello time for the CIST.

hm2AgentStpCstMaxAge.name: hm2AgentStpCstMaxAge
hm2AgentStpCstMaxAge.description: The MSTP root port max age for the CIST.

hm2AgentStpCstRegionalRootId.name: hm2AgentStpCstRegionalRootId
hm2AgentStpCstRegionalRootId.description: The MSTP regional root identifier for the CIST.

hm2AgentStpCstRegionalRootPathCost.name: hm2AgentStpCstRegionalRootPathCost
hm2AgentStpCstRegionalRootPathCost.description: The MSTP regional root path cost for the CIST.

hm2AgentStpCstRootFwdDelay.name: hm2AgentStpCstRootFwdDelay
hm2AgentStpCstRootFwdDelay.description: The MSTP root port forward delay for the CIST.

hm2AgentStpCstBridgeFwdDelay.name: hm2AgentStpCstBridgeFwdDelay
hm2AgentStpCstBridgeFwdDelay.description: The MSTP bridge forward delay for the CIST. The default value is 15.

hm2AgentStpCstBridgeHelloTime.name: hm2AgentStpCstBridgeHelloTime
hm2AgentStpCstBridgeHelloTime.description: The MSTP bridge hello time for the CIST. The default value is 2.

hm2AgentStpCstBridgeHoldTime.name: hm2AgentStpCstBridgeHoldTime
hm2AgentStpCstBridgeHoldTime.description: The MSTP bridge hold time for the CIST.

hm2AgentStpCstBridgeMaxAge.name: hm2AgentStpCstBridgeMaxAge
hm2AgentStpCstBridgeMaxAge.description: The MSTP bridge max age for the CIST. The default value is 20.

hm2AgentStpCstBridgeMaxHops.name: hm2AgentStpCstBridgeMaxHops
hm2AgentStpCstBridgeMaxHops.description: The MSTP bridge max hops for the CIST. The default value is 20.

hm2AgentStpCstBridgePriority.name: hm2AgentStpCstBridgePriority
hm2AgentStpCstBridgePriority.description: The MSTP bridge priority for the CIST. The default value is 32768.

hm2AgentStpCstBridgeHoldCount.name: hm2AgentStpCstBridgeHoldCount
hm2AgentStpCstBridgeHoldCount.description: The MSTP bridge hold count for the CIST. This command sets the value of maximum bpdus that a bridge is allowed to send within a hello time window. The default value is 10.

hm2AgentStpCstPortOperEdge.name: hm2AgentStpCstPortOperEdge
hm2AgentStpCstPortOperEdge.description: The MSTP operational status of a specific port for the CIST.

hm2AgentStpCstPortOperPointToPoint.name: hm2AgentStpCstPortOperPointToPoint
hm2AgentStpCstPortOperPointToPoint.description: The MSTP operational point to point mac of a specific port for the CIST.

hm2AgentStpCstPortTopologyChangeAck.name: hm2AgentStpCstPortTopologyChangeAck
hm2AgentStpCstPortTopologyChangeAck.description: The MSTP topology change acknowledge for a specific port in the CIST.

hm2AgentStpCstPortEdge.name: hm2AgentStpCstPortEdge
hm2AgentStpCstPortEdge.description: The administrative state of a specific port in CIST. enable(1) - enables the port. disable(2) - disables the port. The default port state is disabled.

hm2AgentStpCstPortForwardingState.name: hm2AgentStpCstPortForwardingState
hm2AgentStpCstPortForwardingState.description: The MSTP forwarding state of a specific port in CIST.

hm2AgentStpCstPortId.name: hm2AgentStpCstPortId
hm2AgentStpCstPortId.description: The MSTP port identifier of a specific port in CIST.

hm2AgentStpCstPortPathCost.name: hm2AgentStpCstPortPathCost
hm2AgentStpCstPortPathCost.description: The MSTP port path cost in CIST. The default value will correspond to the recommendation specified in IEEE 802.1s Table 13-2 which varies depending upon link speed.

hm2AgentStpCstPortPriority.name: hm2AgentStpCstPortPriority
hm2AgentStpCstPortPriority.description: The MSTP port priority in CIST. The priority is in the increments of 16. The default value is 128.

hm2AgentStpCstDesignatedBridgeId.name: hm2AgentStpCstDesignatedBridgeId
hm2AgentStpCstDesignatedBridgeId.description: The MSTP designated bridge ID of a specific port in CIST.

hm2AgentStpCstDesignatedCost.name: hm2AgentStpCstDesignatedCost
hm2AgentStpCstDesignatedCost.description: The MSTP designated cost of a specific port in CIST.

hm2AgentStpCstDesignatedPortId.name: hm2AgentStpCstDesignatedPortId
hm2AgentStpCstDesignatedPortId.description: The MSTP designated port ID of a specific port in CIST.

hm2AgentStpCstExtPortPathCost.name: hm2AgentStpCstExtPortPathCost
hm2AgentStpCstExtPortPathCost.description: The MSTP external port path cost in CIST. The default value varies depending upon the link speed.

hm2AgentStpCstPortBpduGuardEffect.name: hm2AgentStpCstPortBpduGuardEffect
hm2AgentStpCstPortBpduGuardEffect.description: BPDU Guard Mode effect on the port. enable(1) - BPDU Guard Mode is enabled on the port. disable(2) - BPDU Guard Mode is disabled on the port.

hm2AgentStpCstPortBpduFilter.name: hm2AgentStpCstPortBpduFilter
hm2AgentStpCstPortBpduFilter.description: This command sets BPDU Filter mode on the port. enable(1) - BPDU Filter Mode is enabled on the port. disable(2) - BPDU Filter Mode is disabled on the port.

hm2AgentStpCstPortBpduFlood.name: hm2AgentStpCstPortBpduFlood
hm2AgentStpCstPortBpduFlood.description: This command sets BPDU Flood mode on the port. enable(1) - BPDU Flood Mode is enabled on the port. disable(2) - BPDU Flood Mode is disabled on the port.

hm2AgentStpCstPortAutoEdge.name: hm2AgentStpCstPortAutoEdge
hm2AgentStpCstPortAutoEdge.description: This command sets the auto-edge mode of the port which enables it to become an edge port if it does not see BPDUs for some duration. enable(1) - enables the auto-edge mode for the port. disable(2) - disables the auto-edge mode for the port. The default auto-edge mode is enabled.

hm2AgentStpCstPortRootGuard.name: hm2AgentStpCstPortRootGuard
hm2AgentStpCstPortRootGuard.description: This command sets a port to discard any superior information received by the port and thus protect against root of the device from changing.The port gets put into discarding state and does not forward any packets. enable(1) - enables the root guard mode for the port. disable(2) - disables the root guard mode for the port. The default root guard mode is disabled.

hm2AgentStpCstPortTCNGuard.name: hm2AgentStpCstPortTCNGuard
hm2AgentStpCstPortTCNGuard.description: This command restricts the port from propagating any topology change information received through that port. enable(1) - enables the TCN guard mode for the port. disable(2) - disables the TCN guard mode for the port. The default TCN guard mode is disabled.

hm2AgentStpCstPortLoopGuard.name: hm2AgentStpCstPortLoopGuard
hm2AgentStpCstPortLoopGuard.description: This command enables loop guard on this port. This setting applies to all Spanning Tree instances of which this port is a member. enable(1) - enables the loop guard mode for the port. disable(2) - disables the loop guard mode for the port. The default loop guard mode is disabled.

hm2AgentStpMstBridgePriority.name: hm2AgentStpMstBridgePriority
hm2AgentStpMstBridgePriority.description: The MSTP bridge priority in a specific instance. The priority is in the increments of 4096. The recommended default value is 32768.

hm2AgentStpMstBridgeIdentifier.name: hm2AgentStpMstBridgeIdentifier
hm2AgentStpMstBridgeIdentifier.description: The MSTP bridge identifier in a specific instance.

hm2AgentStpMstDesignatedRootId.name: hm2AgentStpMstDesignatedRootId
hm2AgentStpMstDesignatedRootId.description: The MSTP designated root bridge identifier in a specific instance.

hm2AgentStpMstRootPathCost.name: hm2AgentStpMstRootPathCost
hm2AgentStpMstRootPathCost.description: The MSTP root path cost in a specific instance.

hm2AgentStpMstRootPortId.name: hm2AgentStpMstRootPortId
hm2AgentStpMstRootPortId.description: The MSTP root port ID in a specific instance.

hm2AgentStpMstTimeSinceTopologyChange.name: hm2AgentStpMstTimeSinceTopologyChange
hm2AgentStpMstTimeSinceTopologyChange.description: The MSTP time since the last topology change in a specific instance.

hm2AgentStpMstTopologyChangeCount.name: hm2AgentStpMstTopologyChangeCount
hm2AgentStpMstTopologyChangeCount.description: The MSTP count of topology changes in a specific instance.

hm2AgentStpMstTopologyChangeParm.name: hm2AgentStpMstTopologyChangeParm
hm2AgentStpMstTopologyChangeParm.description: The MSTP topology change parameter in a specific instance.

hm2AgentStpMstRowStatus.name: hm2AgentStpMstRowStatus
hm2AgentStpMstRowStatus.description: The MSTP instance status. Supported values: active(1) - valid instance. notReady(3) - row has incomplete values. createAndGo(4) - used to create a new instance. destroy(6) - removes an instance.

hm2AgentStpMstPortForwardingState.name: hm2AgentStpMstPortForwardingState
hm2AgentStpMstPortForwardingState.description: The MSTP forwarding state of a specific port in a specific instance.

hm2AgentStpMstPortId.name: hm2AgentStpMstPortId
hm2AgentStpMstPortId.description: The MSTP port identifier of a specific port in a specific instance.

hm2AgentStpMstPortPathCost.name: hm2AgentStpMstPortPathCost
hm2AgentStpMstPortPathCost.description: The MSTP port path cost in a specific instance. The default value will correspond to the recommendation specified in IEEE 802.1s Table 13-2 which varies depending upon link speed.

hm2AgentStpMstPortPriority.name: hm2AgentStpMstPortPriority
hm2AgentStpMstPortPriority.description: The MSTP port priority in a specific instance. The priority is in the increments of 16. The default value is 128.

hm2AgentStpMstDesignatedBridgeId.name: hm2AgentStpMstDesignatedBridgeId
hm2AgentStpMstDesignatedBridgeId.description: The MSTP designated bridge ID of a specific port in a specific instance.

hm2AgentStpMstDesignatedCost.name: hm2AgentStpMstDesignatedCost
hm2AgentStpMstDesignatedCost.description: The MSTP designated cost of a specific port in a specific instance.

hm2AgentStpMstDesignatedPortId.name: hm2AgentStpMstDesignatedPortId
hm2AgentStpMstDesignatedPortId.description: The MSTP designated port ID of a specific port in a specific instance.

hm2AgentStpMstPortLoopInconsistentState.name: hm2AgentStpMstPortLoopInconsistentState
hm2AgentStpMstPortLoopInconsistentState.description: The loop inconsistent state of a specific port in a specific instance. This value can only report as true(1) when loop guard is enabled on the port and the port has transitioned from blocking state in this MST instance.

hm2AgentStpMstPortTransitionsIntoLoopInc.name: hm2AgentStpMstPortTransitionsIntoLoopInconsistentState
hm2AgentStpMstPortTransitionsIntoLoopInc.description: The number of times this interface has transitioned into loop inconsistent state.

hm2AgentStpMstPortTransitionsOutOfLoopIn.name: hm2AgentStpMstPortTransitionsOutOfLoopInconsistentState
hm2AgentStpMstPortTransitionsOutOfLoopIn.description: The number of times this interface has transitioned out of loop inconsistent state.

hm2AgentStpMstPortRole.name: hm2AgentStpMstPortRole
hm2AgentStpMstPortRole.description: The current port pole for a specific port (i.e., root, alternate, designated or backup) in a specific instance.

hm2AgentStpCstAutoPortPathCost.name: hm2AgentStpCstAutoPortPathCost
hm2AgentStpCstAutoPortPathCost.description: The Spanning Tree auto port path cost. If the value is true, the port path cost will be calculated depending on link speed corresponding to the recommendation specified in IEEE 802.1s Table 13-2 which varies depending upon link speed.

hm2AgentStpMstPortReceivedBridgeId.name: hm2AgentStpMstPortReceivedBridgeId
hm2AgentStpMstPortReceivedBridgeId.description: The received bridge ID on a specific port in a specific instance.

hm2AgentStpMstPortReceivedRPC.name: hm2AgentStpMstPortReceivedRPC
hm2AgentStpMstPortReceivedRPC.description: The received root path cost of a specific port in a specific instance.

hm2AgentStpMstPortReceivedPortId.name: hm2AgentStpMstPortReceivedPortId
hm2AgentStpMstPortReceivedPortId.description: The received port ID on a specific port in a specific instance.

hm2AgentStpMstAutoPortPathCost.name: hm2AgentStpMstAutoPortPathCost
hm2AgentStpMstAutoPortPathCost.description: The Spanning Tree auto port path cost of a given instance. If the value is true, the port path cost will be calculated depending on link speed corresponding to the recommendation specified in IEEE 802.1s Table 13-2 which varies depending upon link speed.

hm2AgentStpMstPortReceivedRegionalRPC.name: hm2AgentStpMstPortReceivedRegionalRPC
hm2AgentStpMstPortReceivedRegionalRPC.description: The received regional (internal) root path cost of a specific port in a specific instance.

hm2AgentStpMstVlanRowStatus.name: hm2AgentStpMstVlanRowStatus
hm2AgentStpMstVlanRowStatus.description: The association status of an MSTP instance and a VLAN. Supported values: active(1) - valid association between an MSTP instance and a VLAN. notReady(3) - inconsistent values for the the association between an MSTP instance and a VLAN (VLAN it's not created or version is not MSTP). createAndGo(4) - used to create a new association between an MSTP instance and a VLAN. destroy(6) - removes the association between an MSTP instance and a VLAN.

hm2AgentStpBpduGuardMode.name: hm2AgentStpBpduGuardMode
hm2AgentStpBpduGuardMode.description: The spanning tree BPDU Guard Mode. enable(1) - enables BPDU Guard Mode on the switch. disable(2) - disables BPDU Guard Mode on the switch. The default status is disabled.

hm2AgentStpBpduFilterDefault.name: hm2AgentStpBpduFilterDefault
hm2AgentStpBpduFilterDefault.description: The spanning tree BPDU Filter Mode, it enables BPDU Filter on all edge ports. enable(1) - enables BPDU Filter Mode on the switch. disable(2) - disables BPDU Filter Mode on the switch. The default status is disabled.

hm2AgentStpRingOnlyMode.name: hm2AgentStpRingOnlyMode
hm2AgentStpRingOnlyMode.description: When RSTP Ring Only Mode is enabled the switch ignores the BPDUs age on Ring Only Mode ports. The topology change BPDUs sent on Ring Only Mode ports will have a message age of 1. enable(1) - enables RSTP Ring Only Mode globally. disable(2) - disables RSTP Ring Only Mode globally. The default status is disabled.

hm2AgentStpRingOnlyModeIntfOne.name: hm2AgentStpRingOnlyModeIntfOne
hm2AgentStpRingOnlyModeIntfOne.description: Interface index of the first interface.

hm2AgentStpRingOnlyModeIntfTwo.name: hm2AgentStpRingOnlyModeIntfTwo
hm2AgentStpRingOnlyModeIntfTwo.description: Interface index of the second interface.

hm2AgentStpMstInstanceVlanErrorReturn.name: hm2AgentStpMstInstanceVlanErrorReturn
hm2AgentStpMstInstanceVlanErrorReturn.description: Invalid value for instance. Instance 0 is a system managed instance and the user should not modify it.

hm2AgentStpCstFwdDelayErrorReturn.name: hm2AgentStpCstFwdDelayErrorReturn
hm2AgentStpCstFwdDelayErrorReturn.description: Invalid value combination for Max Age/Forward Delay.

hm2AgentStpMstSwitchVersionConflict.name: hm2AgentStpMstSwitchVersionConflict
hm2AgentStpMstSwitchVersionConflict.description: Cannot switch version while spanning-tree is disabled.

hm2AgentClassOfServicePortTable.name: hm2AgentClassOfServicePortTable
hm2AgentClassOfServicePortTable.description: A table that contains information about the 802.1p priority mapping to traffic class priority queue for every physical port.

hm2AgentClassOfServicePortEntry.name: hm2AgentClassOfServicePortEntry
hm2AgentClassOfServicePortEntry.description: A 802.1p priority mapped to a traffic class priority queue.

hm2AgentClassOfServicePortPriority.name: hm2AgentClassOfServicePortPriority
hm2AgentClassOfServicePortPriority.description: The Priority value determined for the received frame. This value is equivalent to the priority indicated in the tagged frame received, or one of the evaluated priorities, determined according to the media type. For untagged frames received from Ethernet media, this value is equal to the dot1dPortDefaultUserPriority value for the ingress port.

hm2AgentClassOfServicePortClass.name: hm2AgentClassOfServicePortClass
hm2AgentClassOfServicePortClass.description: Traffic class priority queue the received frame is mapped to.

hm2AgentDaiSrcMacValidate.name: hm2AgentDaiSrcMacValidate
hm2AgentDaiSrcMacValidate.description: This object indicates whether Sender MAC validation in the ARP packets is enabled. If this object is set to 'true', validation is enabled. If this object is set to 'false', validation is disabled.

hm2AgentDaiDstMacValidate.name: hm2AgentDaiDstMacValidate
hm2AgentDaiDstMacValidate.description: This object indicates whether Target MAC validation in the ARP Response packets is enabled. If this object is set to 'true', validation is enabled. If this object is set to 'false', validation is disabled.

hm2AgentDaiIPValidate.name: hm2AgentDaiIPValidate
hm2AgentDaiIPValidate.description: This object indicates whether IP address validation in the ARP packets is enabled. If this object is set to 'true', validation is enabled. If this object is set to 'false', validation is disabled.

hm2AgentDaiVlanConfigTable.name: hm2AgentDaiVlanConfigTable
hm2AgentDaiVlanConfigTable.description: A table provides the mechanism to control Dynamic ARP Inspection per VLAN. When a VLAN is created in a device supporting this table, a corresponding entry of this table will be added.

hm2AgentDaiVlanConfigEntry.name: hm2AgentDaiVlanConfigEntry
hm2AgentDaiVlanConfigEntry.description: A row instance contains the configuration for Dynamic ARP Inspection at each existing VLAN.

hm2AgentDaiVlanIndex.name: hm2AgentDaiVlanIndex
hm2AgentDaiVlanIndex.description: This object indicates the VLAN number on which Dynamic ARP Inspection feature is configured.

hm2AgentDaiVlanDynArpInspEnable.name: hm2AgentDaiVlanDynArpInspEnable
hm2AgentDaiVlanDynArpInspEnable.description: This object indicates whether Dynamic ARP Inspection is enabled in this VLAN. If this object is set to 'true', Dynamic ARP Inspection is enabled. If this object is set to 'false', Dynamic ARP Inspection is disabled.

hm2AgentDaiVlanLoggingEnable.name: hm2AgentDaiVlanLoggingEnable
hm2AgentDaiVlanLoggingEnable.description: This object indicates whether the Dynamic ARP Inspection logging is enabled on this VlAN. If this object is set to 'true', Dynamic ARP Inspection logging is enabled. If this object is set to 'false', Dynamic ARP Inspection loging is disabled.

hm2AgentDaiVlanArpAclName.name: hm2AgentDaiVlanArpAclName
hm2AgentDaiVlanArpAclName.description: This object indicates the ARP ACL name set for this VLAN. Notice that the ACL is regarded only if the corresponding row in 'agentArpAclTable' is active.

hm2AgentDaiVlanArpAclStaticFlag.name: hm2AgentDaiVlanArpAclStaticFlag
hm2AgentDaiVlanArpAclStaticFlag.description: If an ARP ACL is defined for the VLAN and there is no match for the received ARP packet, the further proceeding depends on this MIB object. If it is 'true', then the packet is dropped, otherwise the packet is checked against the DHCP snooping bindings database (optional, see 'hm2AgentDaiVlanBindingCheckEnable'). If there is no match in the bindings database too, the packet is dropped.

hm2AgentDaiVlanBindingCheckEnable.name: hm2AgentDaiVlanBindingCheckEnable
hm2AgentDaiVlanBindingCheckEnable.description: If enabled, the ARP frame received on an untrusted port (in a DAI enabled VLAN) is checked against the ARP ACL and the DHCP Snooping bindings database. If disabled it is only checked against the ARP ACL.

hm2AgentDaiStatsReset.name: hm2AgentDaiStatsReset
hm2AgentDaiStatsReset.description: Clear the DAI statistics on all vlans. A value of reset(1) is used to reset the statistics. A read on this object will always return the value none(0). The value none(0) cannot be forcibly set by the administrator.

hm2AgentDaiVlanStatsTable.name: hm2AgentDaiVlanStatsTable
hm2AgentDaiVlanStatsTable.description: A table provides the mechanism to control Dynamic ARP Inspection per VLAN. When a VLAN is created in a device supporting this table, a corresponding entry of this table will be added.

hm2AgentDaiVlanStatsEntry.name: hm2AgentDaiVlanStatsEntry
hm2AgentDaiVlanStatsEntry.description: A row instance contains the Dynamic ARP Inspection statistics per VLAN.

hm2AgentDaiVlanStatsIndex.name: hm2AgentDaiVlanStatsIndex
hm2AgentDaiVlanStatsIndex.description: This object indicates the VLAN number on which Dynamic ARP Inspection statistics are retrieved.

hm2AgentDaiVlanPktsForwarded.name: hm2AgentDaiVlanPktsForwarded
hm2AgentDaiVlanPktsForwarded.description: Number of valid ARP packets forwarded by DAI.

hm2AgentDaiVlanPktsDropped.name: hm2AgentDaiVlanPktsDropped
hm2AgentDaiVlanPktsDropped.description: Number of invalid ARP packets dropped by DAI.

hm2AgentDaiVlanDhcpDrops.name: hm2AgentDaiVlanDhcpDrops
hm2AgentDaiVlanDhcpDrops.description: Number of ARP packets that were dropped by DAI as there is no matching DHCP Snooping binding entry found.

hm2AgentDaiVlanDhcpPermits.name: hm2AgentDaiVlanDhcpPermits
hm2AgentDaiVlanDhcpPermits.description: Number of ARP packets that were forwarded by DAI as there is a matching DHCP Snooping binding entry found.

hm2AgentDaiVlanAclDrops.name: hm2AgentDaiVlanAclDrops
hm2AgentDaiVlanAclDrops.description: Number of ARP packets that were dropped by DAI as there is no matching ARP ACL rule found for this Vlan and the static flag is set on this vlan.

hm2AgentDaiVlanAclPermits.name: hm2AgentDaiVlanAclPermits
hm2AgentDaiVlanAclPermits.description: Number of ARP packets that were permitted by DAI as there is a matching ARP ACL rule found for this Vlan.

hm2AgentDaiVlanSrcMacFailures.name: hm2AgentDaiVlanSrcMacFailures
hm2AgentDaiVlanSrcMacFailures.description: Number of ARP packets that were dropped by DAI as the sender mac address in ARP packet didn't match the source mac in ethernet header.

hm2AgentDaiVlanDstMacFailures.name: hm2AgentDaiVlanDstMacFailures
hm2AgentDaiVlanDstMacFailures.description: Number of ARP packets that were dropped by DAI as the target mac address in ARP reply packet didn't match the destination mac in ethernet header.

hm2AgentDaiVlanIpValidFailures.name: hm2AgentDaiVlanIpValidFailures
hm2AgentDaiVlanIpValidFailures.description: Number of ARP packets that were dropped by DAI as the sender IP address in ARP packet or target IP address in ARP reply packet is invalid. Invalid addresses include 0.0.0.0, 255.255.255.255, IP multicast addresses, class E addresses (240.0.0.0/4), loopback addresses (127.0.0.0/8).

hm2AgentDaiIfConfigTable.name: hm2AgentDaiIfConfigTable
hm2AgentDaiIfConfigTable.description: A table provides the mechanism to configure the trust state for Dynamic ARP Inspection purpose at each physical interface capable of this feature.

hm2AgentDaiIfConfigEntry.name: hm2AgentDaiIfConfigEntry
hm2AgentDaiIfConfigEntry.description: A row instance contains the configuration for Dynamic ARP Inspection at each physical interface capable of this feature.

hm2AgentDaiIfTrustEnable.name: hm2AgentDaiIfTrustEnable
hm2AgentDaiIfTrustEnable.description: This object indicates whether the interface is trusted for Dynamic ARP Inspection purpose. If this object is set to 'true', the interface is trusted. ARP packets coming to this interface will be forwarded without checking. If this object is set to 'false', the interface is not trusted. ARP packets coming to this interface will be subjected to ARP inspection.

hm2AgentDaiIfRateLimit.name: hm2AgentDaiIfRateLimit
hm2AgentDaiIfRateLimit.description: This object indicates rate limit value for Dynamic ARP Inspection purpose. If the incoming rate of ARP packets exceeds the value of this object for consecutively burst interval seconds, ARP packets will be dropped. Value of -1 indicates that there is no rate limit.

hm2AgentDaiIfBurstInterval.name: hm2AgentDaiIfBurstInterval
hm2AgentDaiIfBurstInterval.description: This object indicates the burst interval value for rate limiting purpose on this interface.

hm2AgentDaiIfAutoDisable.name: hm2AgentDaiIfAutoDisable
hm2AgentDaiIfAutoDisable.description: This object indicates whether a port is auto-disabled when the configured ARP threshold is exceeded.

hm2AgentArpAclTable.name: hm2AgentArpAclTable
hm2AgentArpAclTable.description: A table of the ARP ACL entries

hm2AgentArpAclEntry.name: hm2AgentArpAclEntry
hm2AgentArpAclEntry.description: Represents entry for an ARP ACL

hm2AgentArpAclName.name: hm2AgentArpAclName
hm2AgentArpAclName.description: Name of the ARP ACL, which must consist of 1 to 31 alphanumeric characters and uniquely identify this ARP ACL. This object must be set to complete a new ARP ACL row instance.

hm2AgentArpAclRowStatus.name: hm2AgentArpAclRowStatus
hm2AgentArpAclRowStatus.description: The status of this conceptual row. Entries can not be deleted until all rows in arpAclRuleTable with corresponding values of arpAclIndex have been deleted. active(1) - This ACL instance is active. notInService(2) - Row has been suspended. notReady(3) - Row has incomplete values. createAndGo(4) - Accept row values and activate. createAndWait(5) - Accept row values and wait. destroy(6) - Set to this value to delete this instance.

hm2AgentArpAclRuleTable.name: hm2AgentArpAclRuleTable
hm2AgentArpAclRuleTable.description: A table of the ARP ACL Rule entries

hm2AgentArpAclRuleEntry.name: hm2AgentArpAclRuleEntry
hm2AgentArpAclRuleEntry.description: Represents entry for a set of ARP ACL-match rules

hm2AgentArpAclRuleMatchSenderIpAddr.name: hm2AgentArpAclRuleMatchSenderIpAddr
hm2AgentArpAclRuleMatchSenderIpAddr.description: Sender IP address match value for the ARP ACL. This address must be a unicast address unequal to 0.0.0.0.

hm2AgentArpAclRuleMatchSenderMacAddr.name: hm2AgentArpAclRuleMatchSenderMacAddr
hm2AgentArpAclRuleMatchSenderMacAddr.description: Sender MAC address match value for the ARP ACL. This address must be a unicast address unequal to 00:0:00:00:00:00.

hm2AgentArpAclRuleRowStatus.name: hm2AgentArpAclRuleRowStatus
hm2AgentArpAclRuleRowStatus.description: The status of this conceptual row. active(1) - This ACL Rule is active. notInService(2) - Row has been suspended. notReady(3) - Row has incomplete values. createAndGo(4) - Accept row values and activate. createAndWait(5) - Accept row values and wait. destroy(6) - Set to this value to delete an instance.

hm2AgentDhcpSnoopingAdminMode.name: hm2AgentDhcpSnoopingAdminMode
hm2AgentDhcpSnoopingAdminMode.description: This object indicates whether DHCP Snooping is enabled globally. If this object is set to 'true',admin mode is enabled globally. If this object is set to 'false',admin mode is disabled globally.

hm2AgentDhcpSnoopingVerifyMac.name: hm2AgentDhcpSnoopingVerifyMac
hm2AgentDhcpSnoopingVerifyMac.description: This object indicates whether source Mac address in the received DHCP Message needs to be verified or not. If this object is set to 'true',verifyMac is enabled globally. If this object is set to 'false',verifyMac is disabled globally.

hm2AgentDhcpSnoopingVlanConfigTable.name: hm2AgentDhcpSnoopingVlanConfigTable
hm2AgentDhcpSnoopingVlanConfigTable.description: A table provides the mechanism to control DHCP SNOOPING per VLAN. When a VLAN is created in a device supporting this table, a corresponding entry of this table will be added.

hm2AgentDhcpSnoopingVlanConfigEntry.name: hm2AgentDhcpSnoopingVlanConfigEntry
hm2AgentDhcpSnoopingVlanConfigEntry.description: A row instance contains the configuration for DHCP SNOOPING at each existing VLAN.

hm2AgentDhcpSnoopingVlanIndex.name: hm2AgentDhcpSnoopingVlanIndex
hm2AgentDhcpSnoopingVlanIndex.description: This object indicates the VLAN number on which DHCP SNOOPING Inspection feature is configured.

hm2AgentDhcpSnoopingVlanEnable.name: hm2AgentDhcpSnoopingVlanEnable
hm2AgentDhcpSnoopingVlanEnable.description: This object indicates whether DHCP SNOOPING is enabled in this VLAN. If this object is set to 'true', DHCP SNOOPING is enabled. If this object is set to 'false', DHCP SNOOPING is disabled.

hm2AgentDhcpSnoopingIfConfigTable.name: hm2AgentDhcpSnoopingIfConfigTable
hm2AgentDhcpSnoopingIfConfigTable.description: A table provides the mechanism to configure the trust state for DHCP snooping purpose at each physical interface capable of this feature.

hm2AgentDhcpSnoopingIfConfigEntry.name: hm2AgentDhcpSnoopingIfConfigEntry
hm2AgentDhcpSnoopingIfConfigEntry.description: A row instance contains the configuration for DHCP snooping at each physical interface capable of this feature.

hm2AgentDhcpSnoopingIfTrustEnable.name: hm2AgentDhcpSnoopingIfTrustEnable
hm2AgentDhcpSnoopingIfTrustEnable.description: This object indicates whether the interface is trusted for DHCP snooping purpose.

hm2AgentDhcpSnoopingIfLogEnable.name: hm2AgentDhcpSnoopingIfLogEnable
hm2AgentDhcpSnoopingIfLogEnable.description: This object indicates whether the Logging needs on DHCP snooping validations or not

hm2AgentDhcpSnoopingIfRateLimit.name: hm2AgentDhcpSnoopingIfRateLimit
hm2AgentDhcpSnoopingIfRateLimit.description: This object indicates rate limit value for DHCP Snooping purpose. If the incoming rate of DHCP packets exceeds the value of this object for consecutively burst interval seconds, DHCP packets will be dropped. Value of -1 indicates that there is no rate limit.

hm2AgentDhcpSnoopingIfBurstInterval.name: hm2AgentDhcpSnoopingIfBurstInterval
hm2AgentDhcpSnoopingIfBurstInterval.description: This object indicates the burst interval value for rate limiting purpose on this interface.

hm2AgentDhcpSnoopingIfAutoDisable.name: hm2AgentDhcpSnoopingIfAutoDisable
hm2AgentDhcpSnoopingIfAutoDisable.description: This object indicates whether a port is auto-disabled when the configured threshold is reached.

hm2AgentIpsgIfConfigTable.name: hm2AgentIpsgIfConfigTable
hm2AgentIpsgIfConfigTable.description: A table provides the mechanism to configure the IPSG at each physical interface capable of this feature.

hm2AgentIpsgIfConfigEntry.name: hm2AgentIpsgIfConfigEntry
hm2AgentIpsgIfConfigEntry.description: A row instance contains the configuration for IPSG at each physical interface capable of this feature.

hm2AgentIpsgIfVerifySource.name: hm2AgentIpsgIfVerifySource
hm2AgentIpsgIfVerifySource.description: This object indicates whether IP packets received on this interface are filtered based on whether IP Source Guard considers the source IP address to be a valid client address. Setting this variable to false automatically sets hm2AgentIpsgIfPortSecurity to false.

hm2AgentIpsgIfPortSecurity.name: hm2AgentIpsgIfPortSecurity
hm2AgentIpsgIfPortSecurity.description: This object indicates whether IP packets received on this interface are filtered based on whether IP Source Guard considers the source MAC address to be a valid client address. The port security option cannot be enabled unless hm2AgentIpsgIfVerifySource is also enabled. That is, MAC address filtering cannot be done without also doing IP address filtering. But IP address filtering can be done without MAC address filtering. Once the port security option is enabled, it can only be disabled by disabling hm2AgentIpsgIfVerifySource.

hm2AgentDhcpSnoopingStatsReset.name: hm2AgentDhcpSnoopingStatsReset
hm2AgentDhcpSnoopingStatsReset.description: Clear the DHCP snooping statistics on all ports. A value of reset(1) is used to reset the statistics. A read on this object will always return the value none(0). The value none(0) cannot be forcibly set by the administrator.

hm2AgentDhcpSnoopingStatsTable.name: hm2AgentDhcpSnoopingStatsTable
hm2AgentDhcpSnoopingStatsTable.description: A table provides the mechanism for statics of DHCP snooping.

hm2AgentDhcpSnoopingStatsEntry.name: hm2AgentDhcpSnoopingStatsEntry
hm2AgentDhcpSnoopingStatsEntry.description: A row instance contains the DHCP snooping statistics per VLAN.

hm2AgentDhcpSnoopingMacVerifyFailures.name: hm2AgentDhcpSnoopingMacVerifyFailures
hm2AgentDhcpSnoopingMacVerifyFailures.description: This object indicates the number of failure verifications of client mac address with source mac address

hm2AgentDhcpSnoopingInvalidClientMessage.name: hm2AgentDhcpSnoopingInvalidClientMessages
hm2AgentDhcpSnoopingInvalidClientMessage.description: This object indicates the number of invalid DHCP releases and deny messages

hm2AgentDhcpSnoopingInvalidServerMessage.description: This object indicates the number of invalid DHCP server mesaages
